<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Johnston, John. Description of the Country around Lakes Superior and Huron, 1809. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0018</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p class="positiveIndent">The Fall of S<sup>t</sup> Marys is found to lie in 46, 45<sup>m</sup> North Latitude and 63, 35<sup>m</sup> West Longitude<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It is the only <span class="AddHand-author">apparent</span> outlet for the Redundant waters of Lake Superior, the vast extent of which, being more than twelve hundred miles in circumference, makes it very problematical how it can answer the purpose especially When it is considered that innumerable Streams and many Rivers nearly of equal Size with the fall deposit their waters in that great inland Ocean<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Were I to hazard an Opinion on the subject, I should think the frequent and almost <span class="AddHand-editors">[i]</span>mpenetrable fogs which prevail on the Lake during the Summer, which eschalations, are generally carried off by strong and cold northwesterly winds, which from its position, sweep it lengthwise, must have a considerable effect<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  But I shall have something farther to say on this phenomenon when I come to speak more particularly of the Lake and the quality of its wa<span class="AddHand-editors">[ters.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The fall is about half a mile in length and a m<span class="AddHand-editors">[ile]</span> in breadth including the Islands on each side<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  On the farthest stream on the north side the No<span class="AddHand-editors">[rth]</span> West C<sup>o</sup> have a fine Saw Mill<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Here they have also Several Houses and Stores for the Reception of their Goods from Montreal their Vessels coming to ancho<span class="AddHand-editors">[r]</span> within 300 yd<sup>s</sup> of the Quay<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Goods are Carted ne<span class="AddHand-editors">[ar]</span> the Portage which is half a mile in length, and deposited in a Store from whence the ar<span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[1]</span></p>

